623
00:39:17,519 --> 00:39:19,839
to think that a man could live such a double life

624
00:39:19,839 --> 00:39:21,739
and that beneath the tatters of a beggar

625
00:39:21,739 --> 00:39:23,919
there should lurk a respectable gentleman.

626
00:39:24,219 --> 00:39:25,759
It is as though one of Dickens' tears

627
00:39:25,759 --> 00:39:27,799
had sprung to life before our very eyes.

628
00:39:28,559 --> 00:39:29,839
You are right, Watson.

629
00:39:30,159 --> 00:39:32,879
It is a tale for the penny magazines.

630
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:37,099
Yet it illustrates a principle I have long held

631
00:39:37,099 --> 00:39:40,039
that appearances are but the surface of things

632
00:39:40,039 --> 00:39:44,059
and that beneath the mask of poverty may lie the craft of wealth

633
00:39:44,059 --> 00:39:48,280
